---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import Section from '../components/Section.astro';
import LearningPathwayDiagram from '../components/LearningPathwayDiagram.astro';

const futureFields = ['Medicine', 'Dentistry', 'Pharmacy', 'Law', 'AI & Digital Transformation', 'Business & Leadership'];
---
<Base
  title="Academia Europa · European Professional Education Institution"
  description="A European institution for structured postgraduate professional education. Specialised academies, evidence-informed programmes, and academic governance across professional fields."
>
  <!-- Hero -->
  <section class="bg-ivory border-b border-platinum-soft/60">
    <div class="container-prose py-32 md:py-44">
      <div class="eyebrow mb-8">A European Institution for Postgraduate Professional Education</div>
      <h1 class="font-serif text-navy-deep text-5xl md:text-7xl leading-[1.02] max-w-5xl">
        A European Institution for Structured Professional Mastery.
      </h1>
      <p class="mt-10 max-w-5xl text-lg md:text-xl leading-relaxed text-graphite">
        Academia Europa is a European professional education institution operated by Solex Education Unipessoal LDA, Portugal. It develops structured, evidence-based postgraduate learning pathways for experienced professionals across specialised fields, beginning with veterinary medicine through Veterinary Academy International.
      </p>
      <div class="mt-12 flex flex-wrap gap-4">
        <a href="/academies" class="btn">Explore Our Academies</a>
        <a href="/partnerships" class="btn">Academic Review & Partnerships</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <Section eyebrow="Our Approach" title="Beyond Fragmented Learning.">
    <div class="prose-editorial max-w-5xl">
      <p>In many professions, continuing education has become fragmented: isolated webinars, disconnected lectures, certificates without progression. Academia Europa was created to offer a more structured path: one that helps experienced professionals build mastery through carefully designed learning architecture, expert instruction, and disciplined academic standards.</p>
      <p>We are not a marketplace of courses. We are a European institution shaping a long-term ecosystem of professional education.</p>
    </div>
  </Section>

  <Section eyebrow="Professional Academies" title="Specialised academies, one institutional home." tone="ivory">
    <div class="prose-editorial max-w-5xl">
      <p>Academia Europa is designed as the institutional home for specialised professional academies. Each academy focuses on a defined professional field while sharing a common commitment to structured learning, evidence-informed education, academic documentation, ethical communication, and professional relevance.</p>
      <div class="mt-8">
        <a href="/academies" class="btn">View Professional Academies</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </Section>

  <Section eyebrow="Beginning with Veterinary Medicine" title="Veterinary Academy International.">
    <div class="prose-editorial max-w-5xl">
      <p>Veterinary Academy International is the first specialised academy of Academia Europa, dedicated to structured postgraduate veterinary education and professional development. Programme directions, faculty information, and full course detail are available on the dedicated VAI platform.</p>
      <div class="mt-8 flex flex-wrap gap-4">
        <a href="/academies/vai" class="btn">Discover VAI</a>
        <a href="https://vai.vet" rel="noopener" class="btn">Visit VAI</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </Section>

  <Section eyebrow="A Multi-Disciplinary Platform in Development" title="Designed to extend across professional fields." tone="ivory">
    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-12 gap-12 items-start">
      <div class="md:col-span-7 prose-editorial">
        <p>Academia Europa begins with veterinary medicine through VAI, while its long-term architecture is designed to support specialised academies across additional professional fields. Each future academy will be developed with field-specific experts, appropriate academic documentation, and professional review standards.</p>
      </div>
      <ul class="md:col-span-5 grid grid-cols-2 gap-x-6 gap-y-3">
        {futureFields.map((f) => (
          <li class="border-t border-platinum pt-2 text-navy-deep font-serif text-lg">{f}</li>
        ))}
      </ul>
    </div>
  </Section>

  <Section eyebrow="Learning Pathways" title="Foundation. Mastery. Leadership." align="center">
    <LearningPathwayDiagram />
  </Section>

  <Section eyebrow="Academic Discipline" title="Standards and governance, documented." tone="ivory">
    <div class="prose-editorial max-w-5xl">
      <p>Academia Europa programmes are developed with defined learning objectives, structured modules, faculty documentation, evidence-level distinctions, assessment design, and review cycles. The model supports CPD/CE alignment and external professional review where applicable, with any recognition stated clearly once formally granted.</p>
      <div class="mt-8 flex flex-wrap gap-4">
        <a href="/academic-standards" class="btn">Academic Standards</a>
        <a href="/academic-governance" class="btn">Academic Governance</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </Section>

  <Section eyebrow="Institutional Commitment" title="Built to outlast trends and individuals.">
    <div class="prose-editorial max-w-5xl">
      <p>Academia Europa is being developed as a long-term European platform for structured postgraduate professional education. Its work is guided by academic discipline, professional relevance, ethical communication, and a commitment to responsible learning across specialised fields.</p>
    </div>
  </Section>

  <section class="bg-navy-deep text-ivory">
    <div class="container-prose py-28 text-center">
      <div class="eyebrow text-champagne-soft mb-6">For Professionals, Faculty, and Institutions</div>
      <h2 class="font-serif text-ivory text-3xl md:text-5xl leading-tight max-w-3xl mx-auto">
        Academia Europa welcomes practitioners seeking structured growth, educators committed to meaningful teaching, and institutions exploring academic collaboration.
      </h2>
      <div class="mt-12 flex flex-wrap gap-4 justify-center">
        <a href="/partnerships" class="btn btn-light">Academic Review & Partnerships</a>
        <a href="/contact" class="btn btn-light">Contact Academia Europa</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Base>
